FBIS4-39701 "drsov112_a_94024" FBIS-SOV-94-112 Daily Report 9 Jun 1994 RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Karasin on Right To Protect Servicemen in Tajikistan Karasin on Right To Protect Servicemen in Tajikistan LD0906163794 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1502 GMT 9 Jun 94 LD0906163794 Moscow INTERFAX English BFN [From the "Diplomatic Panorama" feature: Igor Porshnev, Vitaly Trubetskoi and others] [Text] Moscow reserves the right to use every tool at its disposal to protect its servicemen and other Russians in Tajikistan. Grigory Karasin, Russian Foreign Ministry spokesman, said at a Moscow briefing Thursday that armed terror had been and would be dealt with resolutely. He said that the recent killings of Russian servicemen and ethnic Russians in Tajikistan was the work of those who did not want peace and stability in that country. Karasin also said that at its emergency meeting the Tajik government had decided to take up numerous steps to protect the Russians and the residents of the Tajik capital. Round the clock patrolling had been introduced in areas inhabited by Russians. Investigation teams in which military prosecutors are represented have been set up.
